title: Mt Macedon: Body found in bushland | Cairns Post
text:
Use keywords to search content on this website Search Use keywords to search content on this website media_camera A crime scene has been established at Mt Macedon, as Victorian detectives investigate the discovery of a badly decomposed body. Picture: Laurel Irving / 7 News Melbourne Badly decomposed body found in Mt Macedon, Victoria Kim Stephens, news.com.au February 20, 2017 3:24pm 
A CRIME scene has been established in central Victorian bushland where a badly decomposed body has been found. 
The remains were discovered about 12.30pm in bushland near Mount Macedon, about 65km north of Melbourne. 
A Victoria Police spokeswoman said the remains would be forensically tested to determine an identity and to try to establish the cause of death. More to come.
